<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 7:55AM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A line of showers and thunderstorms will impact portions of
Forsyth, Davidson and Stanly Counties through 900 AM EDT...
At 754 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms from Mount Airy to Charlotte, moving northeast at 55
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 35 mph. Very heavy rainfall.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, Lexington, Albemarle, Badin Lake, Thomasville,
Kernersville, Clemmons, Bermuda Run, Linwood and Plyler.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
